<TITLE> New CJ to take oath Wednesday </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 22 (bdnews24.com)  Newly appointed chief justice Mohammed Tafazzul Islam will take oath Wednesday. President Zillur Rahman will administer the oath at Bangabhaban at 9:30am, Md Shawkat Hossain, registrar of the Supreme Court told bdnews24.com. The president appointed Islam on Dec 15 ahead of MM Ruhul Amin's retirement. Outgoing chief justice Amin met the president at Bangabhaban on his last day in office Tuesday. The president lauded Amin on his time in office and hoped that his contribution in establishing justice and rule of law would be followed by others. Amin assumed the office on June 1 this year. Islam was appointed as a judge in the Appellate Division of the Supreme Court on Aug 27, 2003. He will go into retirement on Feb 7, 2010. bd
